"index_reference": "4802",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A disease ruinous to crops. In the OT blight was seen as evidence of God's judgment.</p>\n<h2>Blight as punishment from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:22\">DEU 28:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos9:16\">HOS 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos4:9\">AMO 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag2:17\">HAG 2:17</a></p>\n<h2>Deliverance from blight</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:37-1Kgs8:39\">1KI 8:37–8:39</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:28-2Chr6:30\">2CH 6:28–6:30</a></p>\n<h2>Blight as a symbol of sorrow</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:4\">PSA 102:4</a></strong></p>",
